{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "08", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "26", "S": "32"}}, "news": [{"title": "NGT refuses to stay Telangana government's Future City project, calls for counters", "para": "The National Green Tribunal's southern zone bench refused to halt the Telangana government's Future City Project, directing authorities to file responses. An environmentalist had petitioned, alleging development began without mandatory environmental clearances. The tribunal adjourned the case for further hearing on June 9.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/ngt-rejects-stay-on-telanganas-future-city-project-amid-environmental-concerns/130101166?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-197544/130101166.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Haryana: After HC stay on S+4, town planning asks HSVP how infrastructure funds were used", "para": "Haryana has paused all stilt-plus-four construction approvals. This follows a court stay and concerns over infrastructure capacity. The town and country planning department is now demanding a report on how 689 crore rupees were spent on upgrades. This money was meant for infrastructure linked to increased density. The court highlighted the strain on services like sewage and traffic.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/high-court-stay-on-haryanas-s4-construction-infrastructure-fund-utilization-under-scrutiny/130101036?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-59272/130101036.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Ghaziabad: GDA makes rooftop solar panels space in building maps must for approval", "para": "Ghaziabad mandates rooftop solar panel space in building maps, rejecting non-compliant submissions. A refundable fee, tiered by plot size, is required for map approval under the PM Surya Ghar scheme. This initiative aims to make Ghaziabad a solar city, targeting 10% renewable energy by 2027.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/ghaziabad-mandates-rooftop-solar-panel-spaces-in-building-plans-for-developers/130101002?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-107818/130101002.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}